<br>
Hecate looked around the room, as if expecting something.  Not known for her patience, she called out.<br>
<br>
::Sisters, I know you can hear me.  And I know you know why I'm here.  Don't be difficult.  Give me what I want and I will trouble you no more.  <br>
<br>
Suddenly, a unison of voices could be heard, whispy yet clear, carried upon some unseen wind.<br>
<br>
::You use our relationship too loosely &quot;sister&quot;.  How dare you come in here without our permission, and have the audacity to claim what is rightfully ours.  Remember who you are dealing with.  Leave now before it is too late.<br>
<br>
This really rubbed Hecate the wrong way.  She threw her arms into the air, while her hair blew crazily behind her.  Shouting the words of a powerful spell, a greenish halo auddenly enveloped her.  She pointed at the walls on either side of her, and blasts of verdant flames flew from her fingertips.  The defenseless walls fell with agonizing wails and groans.<br>
<br>
Then suddenly the debris of rocks sprang back, rebuilding what had been destroyed.  <br>
<br>
::Hecate, do not be as stupid as that.  We can always undo what you destroy, for we control destiny, we manipulate time.  The only reason we have not returned &quot;in favor&quot; is because we all have agreed to an immortal vow never to harm another.  Don't make us break that promise, for you will be the first to taste our wrath!<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hecategoddessofmagic>Hecate Goddess of Magic</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(4/23/03 12:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=313.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://nefaria.com/gallery/1152x864/art/sorceress1152.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Within the Temple</span><hr size=1> ::The vow binds us all, from the lowliest dryad to the loftliest deity.  I will not break this binding, but I will get what I want!!  I have seen the future, and it is bleek.  What I do, I do for us all.  If I should fade from this realm, so goes you three.  Now hand over my thread, and I will be gone.<br>
<br>
Laughter permeated the chamber, echoing and bouncing off the walls.  Hecate was furious.  How dare they ridicule her!  She would have torn the temple asunder, brick from brick, but she knew it would be futile.  So she stood there in silent fury, as the sunds of laughter gradually faded away.<br>
<br>
The symphony of voices began again, although mockingly.<br>
<br>
